🐹 Assignment Case
Guinea Pig Breeding Manager
Story
You have just been hired as a junior Java developer by a small breeding company called Nordic Guinea Farm.
The farm breeds guinea pigs for pet shops and private buyers across Scandinavia.
Until now, the breeder has stored all information about the animals in simple spreadsheet files.
Unfortunately, the system has become difficult to manage, and important data has been lost.
To solve this problem, the breeder wants a Java application that can manage the herd locally.

The application must:
Load guinea pig data from a CSV file
Allow the breeder to view the herd
Sort animals by different attributes
Support different types of guinea pigs
Save updated data back to a CSV file

Because the system will later be integrated into a larger animal management platform,
it must be designed using clean Object-Oriented Programming principles.

Program Requirements
Your program must allow the breeder to:
1️⃣ Automatically load guinea pigs
When the program starts, it must:
Read guinea pig data from a CSV file
Store the animals in an ArrayList

2️⃣ Support multiple guinea pig types
The breeder works with different breeding categories:
Type	Description
PetGuineaPig	Normal guinea pigs sold as pets
ShowGuineaPig	Special guinea pigs used in competitions

